 Port Elizabeth - The Family Violence Child Protection and Sexual Offences Unit in Port Elizabeth is urgently trying to trace a 14-year-old girl, who walked out of a Place of Safety on 21 June 2019 and never returned. According to police information, Ntombizanele Jakuja walked out of the Erica House Place of Safety in Port Elizabeth informing friends that she will return after the school holidays. "She allegedly went to live with her boyfriend in Central," described police spokesperson, Colonel Priscilla Naidu. "However, no one knows, who he is or where he lives. "She has since not returned to the Place of Safety. Her mother lives in Sidwell." Col Naidu said that anyone, who may have seen her or may know of her whereabouts is asked to contact D/Sgt Sonica Van der Merwe on 071 475 2309 or 041 401 3000 or Crime Stop 08600 10111 or their nearest police station. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 